023-04-05T17:23:20Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "This type\r\n```rust\r\n#[repr(transparent)]\r\nstruct S(u8);\r\n```\r\n[has a \"preferred\" alignment of 8](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=c92056b343c94ceefc4d704cff09eb27), but `u8`'s \"preferred\" alignment is 1. I would expect such a transparent newtype to preserve \"preferred\" alignment.\r\n\r\nPreferred alignment is not directly visible to Rust programs, it's an internal thing inside the compiler, so this is not a big deal -- but it is still surprising.\r\nCc @oli-obk @eddyb ", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/109560/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/109560/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}